      "Lisbon's agricultural heritage remains visible across the landscape, with active farms and former agricultural properties that feature the long driveways, barn access roads, and equipment storage areas common to Connecticut's working rural towns. Many of these properties benefit from our gravel and recycled asphalt milling installation services, which provide durable, well-draining surfaces for access roads and work areas where hot-mix asphalt would be either impractical or unnecessarily expensive. For primary residential driveways, we install quality hot-mix asphalt over engineered bases that account for Lisbon's specific soil conditions — a mix of sandy glacial deposits and heavier clay soils that vary across the town and require individualized treatment. Northeast Paving also provides excavation and grading services for Lisbon property owners developing new home sites, expanding existing driveways, or addressing drainage problems that threaten their pavement or structures.",
